title: school athletes of the week
text:
The Dispatch high-school Athletes of the Week, based on performances of Oct. 5-11:
Ellee Bullock DUBLIN JEROME, GIRLS TENNIS Bullock, a senior who has committed to Utah State, won the Division I Central District singles championship with a 6-2, 6-2 win in the final over Alexia Meyer of Olentangy Liberty.
Deric Williamson CENTRAL CROSSING, FOOTBALL Williamson, a junior quarterback, completed 33 of 49 passes for 388 yards and five touchdowns to rally the Comets past Dublin Coffman 48-42 in overtime. He also ran for 52 yards and a TD.
Bullock and Williamson will receive plaques from Motorists Insurance. Coaches are encouraged to email sports@dispatch.com or fax 614-461-8798 by 4 p.m. Mondays with nominations.
In addition to the two Athletes of the Week, The Dispatch recognizes a top performer in each sport in season:
Mitchell Bergman HARTLEY, BOYS SOCCER Bergman, a junior forward, had two goals and an assist in a 7-1 win over London and single goals in a 1-0 win over Watterson and a 2-0 win over Jonathan Alder.
Bailey Waitkus WHETSTONE, GIRLS SOCCER Waitkus, a junior center-midfielder, helped the Braves win their fourth consecutive City League championship with two goals and an assist in a 5-0 victory over Centennial at Mapfre Stadium.
Andy Payne THOMAS WORTHINGTON, BOYS CROSS COUNTRY Payne, a sophomore, finished second out of 211 runners in 15:32, leading the Cardinals to the championship in a Thomas Worthington invitational with 57 points.
India Johnson HILLIARD DAVIDSON, GIRLS CROSS COUNTRY Johnson, a junior, finished first out of 220 runners in 19:04.29 in the Darby Dash at Hilliard Darby, leading the Wildcats to the team title with 42 points.
Caleb Davern CENTRAL CROSSING, BOYS GOLF Davern, a freshman, shot 3-under-par 69 to tie for first in leading the Comets to a Division I sectional championship at Turnberry Golf Course.
Micah Vincent WORTHINGTON KILBOURNE, GIRLS GOLF Vincent, a senior, shot 3-over-par 75 for medalist honors in leading the Wolves to a third-place finish in a Division I sectional at Mentel Memorial Golf Course.
Ashlyn Leon DUBLIN SCIOTO, GIRLS VOLLEYBALL Leon, a senior defensive specialist, had 32 digs and one ace in a 3-1 victory over Dublin Jerome and 30 digs, three aces and one kill in a 3-2 victory over Hilliard Darby.
Hana Sinno THOMAS WORTHINGTON, FIELD HOCKEY Sinno, a senior, scored the winning goal in overtime and had an assist in a 2-1 win over Watterson. She also had a goal and an assist in a 6-0 victory over Lancaster.
